### Example 14: Betti numbers of a triangle (hollow — edges only)

3 vertices, 3 edges forming a cycle, no face: β₀ = 1, β₁ = 1 (one loop).

```scheme
(define triangle-loop
  (topo/complex
    (list 0 1 2)
    (list (list 0 1) (list 1 2) (list 2 0))
    (list)))

(topo/betti triangle-loop)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the vector `(1 1 0)`]

