### Example 15: Betti numbers of a filled triangle

Same 3 vertices, 3 edges, but now fill it with the 2-face (0 1 2): β₁ = 0 (the loop is filled in).

```scheme
(define filled-triangle
  (topo/complex
    (list 0 1 2)
    (list (list 0 1) (list 1 2) (list 2 0))
    (list (list 0 1 2))))

(topo/betti filled-triangle)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the vector `(1 0 0)`]

<!-- BUILD: run on interpreter; filling the triangle removes the 1-hole; output is (1 0 0) -->

