### Example 16: Betti numbers of a tetrahedron surface (2-sphere)

4 vertices, 6 edges, 4 triangular faces: β₀ = 1, β₁ = 0, β₂ = 1 (one 2-dimensional void enclosed by the surface).

```scheme
(define tet-surface
  (topo/complex
    (list 0 1 2 3)
    (list (list 0 1) (list 0 2) (list 0 3) (list 1 2) (list 1 3) (list 2 3))
    (list (list 0 1 2) (list 0 1 3) (list 0 2 3) (list 1 2 3))))

(topo/betti tet-surface)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the vector `(1 0 1)`]

<!-- BUILD: run on interpreter; a tetrahedron surface is a 2-sphere, β₂ = 1; output is (1 0 1) -->

---

### Example 17: Betti numbers of a torus (minimal triangulation)

A torus has β₀ = 1, β₁ = 2 (two independent loops: around the hole and around the tube), β₂ = 1.

```scheme
; Same torus from Example 6
(define torus-betti
  (topo/complex torus-vertices torus-edges torus-faces))

(topo/betti torus-betti)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the vector `(1 2 1)`]

<!-- BUILD: run on interpreter; torus has two independent 1-cycles and one 2-cavity; output is (1 2 1) -->

