### Example 18: Betti numbers of a wedge of two circles

Two circles glued at a point: β₀ = 1, β₁ = 2 (two independent loops), β₂ = 0.

```scheme
; Circle 1: vertices 0,1,2; edges (0 1) (1 2) (2 0)
; Circle 2: vertices 0,3,4; edges (0 3) (3 4) (4 0)
; They share vertex 0
(define wedge-two-circles
  (topo/complex
    (list 0 1 2 3 4)
    (list (list 0 1) (list 1 2) (list 2 0)
          (list 0 3) (list 3 4) (list 4 0))
    (list)))

(topo/betti wedge-two-circles)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the vector `(1 2 0)`]

<!-- BUILD: run on interpreter; two loops joined at a point → β₁ = 2; output is (1 2 0) -->

---

### Example 19: Betti number β₀ counts connected components

A complex with 3 disjoint edges (3 components): β₀ = 3.

```scheme
(define three-edges
  (topo/complex
    (list 0 1 2 3 4 5)
    (list (list 0 1) (list 2 3) (list 4 5))
    (list)))

(topo/betti three-edges)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the vector `(3 0 0)`]

