### Example 20: Betti numbers distinguish homotopy types

A sphere and a torus have different Betti numbers, so they are not homotopy equivalent (and hence not homeomorphic).

```scheme
(define sphere-betti (topo/betti tet-surface))    ; (1 0 1)
(define torus-betti-val (topo/betti torus-betti))  ; (1 2 1)

(list \"Sphere\" sphere-betti \"Torus\" torus-betti-val)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows `(Sphere (1 0 1) Torus (1 2 1))`]

<!-- BUILD: run on interpreter; different Betti sequences → different topologies; output is the comparison list -->

---

### Example 21: Computing individual Betti number β_k

The verb `topo/betti-k` computes just the *k*-th Betti number.

```scheme
(define torus-b1 (topo/betti-k torus-betti 1))
torus-b1
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the number `2`]

