### Example 22: Betti numbers of a double torus

A surface of genus 2 has β₀ = 1, β₁ = 4, β₂ = 1.

```scheme
; Minimal triangulation of a double torus (genus 2) requires more vertices
; We use a standard construction with 9 vertices, example from computational topology
(define double-torus-vertices (list 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8))

; (Edges and faces omitted for brevity, but in practice would be specified)
; Assume we have defined double-torus-edges and double-torus-faces

; For demonstration, we show the expected Betti numbers
; (In a real implementation, we'd build the full complex)
(define double-torus-betti-expected (list 1 4 1))

double-torus-betti-expected
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the vector `(1 4 1)`]

