### Example 23: Relationship between Euler characteristic and Betti numbers

For a finite simplicial complex, χ = β₀ − β₁ + β₂ − β₃ + … (alternating sum).

```scheme
(define (betti-to-euler betti-vec)
  (let loop ((bs betti-vec) (sign 1) (sum 0))
    (if (null? bs)
        sum
        (loop (cdr bs) (- sign) (+ sum (* sign (car bs)))))))

(define torus-euler (betti-to-euler (list 1 2 1)))
torus-euler  ; Should be 0
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the number `0`]

<!-- BUILD: run on interpreter; χ = 1 − 2 + 1 = 0 for torus; output is 0 -->

---

### Example 24: Betti numbers of a simplicial complex from data (small example)

Given 5 points in the plane, build a Vietoris-Rips complex at a fixed radius and compute Betti numbers.

```scheme
(define points
  (list (list 0 0) (list 1 0) (list 0 1) (list 1 1) (list 0.5 0.5)))

(define rips-complex (topo/vietoris-rips points 1.5))

(topo/betti rips-complex)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows a Betti vector, e.g., `(1 1 0)` if the points form a loop]

<!-- BUILD: run on interpreter; `topo/vietoris-rips` builds a simplicial complex from point cloud; `topo/betti` computes holes; output depends on the configuration, expected (1 1 0) or similar -->

---

### Example 25: Betti curve — tracking Betti numbers across filtration

A Betti curve shows how β_k changes as a parameter (radius, density threshold) varies.

```scheme
(define radii (list 0.5 1.0 1.5 2.0))

(define betti-at-radii
  (map (lambda (r)
         (list r (topo/betti (topo/vietoris-rips points r))))
       radii))

betti-at-radii
```

