### Example 31: Checking orientability of a surface complex

A closed surface is orientable if it can be given a consistent orientation on all faces. The verb `topo/orientable?` checks this.

```scheme
(define tet-orientable (topo/orientable? tet-surface))
tet-orientable  ; #t (sphere is orientable)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the boolean `#t`]

