### Example 32: Building a non-orientable surface (Möbius band)

A Möbius band is a 2-complex that is non-orientable. We can build a triangulation.

```scheme
; Möbius band: 6 vertices, 9 edges, 4 triangles (minimal triangulation)
(define mobius-vertices (list 0 1 2 3 4 5))

(define mobius-edges
  (list (list 0 1) (list 1 2) (list 2 0)  ; first triangle boundary
        (list 2 3) (list 3 4) (list 4 2)  ; second
        (list 4 5) (list 5 0) (list 0 4)  ; third (twist)
        ))

(define mobius-faces
  (list (list 0 1 2) (list 2 3 4) (list 4 5 0)))

(define mobius (topo/complex mobius-vertices mobius-edges mobius-faces))

(topo/orientable? mobius)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the boolean `#f`]

<!-- BUILD: run on interpreter; Möbius band is non-orientable; output is #f -->

