### Example 35: The complete graph K₄ as a simplicial complex

K₄ has 4 vertices, 6 edges. If we add all 4 possible triangular faces (and the tetrahedron), it's a filled tetrahedron.

```scheme
(define k4-filled
  (topo/complex
    (list 0 1 2 3)
    (list (list 0 1) (list 0 2) (list 0 3) (list 1 2) (list 1 3) (list 2 3))
    (list (list 0 1 2) (list 0 1 3) (list 0 2 3) (list 1 2 3))
    (list (list 0 1 2 3))))

(topo/betti k4-filled)  ; (1 0 0 0) — contractible
```

