### Example 36: Checking planarity via topology

A complex that is a planar graph embedded in the plane (with faces added) should have χ = 2.

```scheme
(define planar-graph
  (topo/complex
    (list 0 1 2 3)
    (list (list 0 1) (list 1 2) (list 2 3) (list 3 0) (list 0 2))
    (list (list 0 1 2) (list 0 2 3))))  ; two faces (plus unbounded outer face in the plane)

(topo/euler-char planar-graph)  ; 4 - 5 + 2 = 1 (for the complex itself, outer face not counted)
```

