### Example 39: Number of connected components from f-vector and Euler characteristic

For a graph (1-dimensional complex), β₀ = 1 + (f₁ − f₀) via the formula χ = f₀ − f₁ = β₀ − β₁ when β₁ = 0.

```scheme
(define tree-complex
  (topo/complex
    (list 0 1 2 3)
    (list (list 0 1) (list 1 2) (list 2 3))
    (list)))

(define f (topo/f-vector tree-complex))  ; (4 3)
(define chi (topo/euler-char tree-complex))  ; 4 - 3 = 1

(list \"f-vector\" f \"chi\" chi \"β₀\" (car (topo/betti tree-complex)))
```

