### Example 51: Detecting the number of clusters via dimension-0 persistence

The number of long bars in dimension 0 indicates the number of clusters.

```scheme
(define cluster-pts
  (list (list 0 0) (list 0.1 0) (list 5 0) (list 5.1 0)))

(define cluster-filt
  (map (lambda (r) (topo/vietoris-rips cluster-pts r))
       (list 0.05 0.2 1.0 3.0 6.0)))

(define cluster-pers (topo/persistence cluster-filt))

; Filter dimension-0 features with long life
(define clusters
  (filter (lambda (p)
            (and (= (car p) 0)
                 (> (- (caddr p) (cadr p)) 2.0)))
          cluster-pers))

(length clusters)  ; Should be 2 (two clusters)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the number `2`]

<!-- BUILD: run on interpreter; two widely separated pairs of points → two persistent components; output is 2 -->

