### Example 52: Persistence in dimension 2 (voids)

A 3D point cloud with a cavity (e.g., points on a sphere surface) will show a dimension-2 feature.

```scheme
; 8 points at corners of a cube (hollow)
(define cube-corners
  (list (list 0 0 0) (list 1 0 0) (list 0 1 0) (list 1 1 0)
        (list 0 0 1) (list 1 0 1) (list 0 1 1) (list 1 1 1)))

(define cube-filt
  (map (lambda (r) (topo/vietoris-rips cube-corners r))
       (list 0.5 1.0 1.5 2.0)))

(define cube-pers (topo/persistence cube-filt))

; Look for dimension-2 features
(filter (lambda (p) (= (car p) 2)) cube-pers)
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows dimension-2 birth-death pairs]

