### Example 53: Persistent homology of a torus point cloud

Sample points on a torus surface; expect two dimension-1 features (two independent loops) and one dimension-2 feature (the enclosed volume).

```scheme
; Simplified: 12 points arranged roughly in a torus shape (major and minor circles)
(define torus-sample
  (list (list 2 0 0) (list 0 2 0) (list -2 0 0) (list 0 -2 0)
        (list 2 0 0.5) (list 0 2 0.5) (list -2 0 0.5) (list 0 -2 0.5)
        (list 1.5 0 0.3) (list 0 1.5 0.3) (list -1.5 0 0.3) (list 0 -1.5 0.3)))

(define torus-filt
  (map (lambda (r) (topo/vietoris-rips torus-sample r))
       (list 1.0 2.0 3.0 4.0)))

(define torus-pers-data (topo/persistence torus-filt))

; Count long-lived dimension-1 features
(length (filter (lambda (p)
                  (and (= (car p) 1)
                       (> (- (caddr p) (cadr p)) 1.0)))
                torus-pers-data))
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, array display mode, shows the count of persistent 1-cycles]

