### Example 55: Comparing persistence of two datasets

Use bottleneck distance to quantify similarity.

```scheme
(define data-A (list (list 0 0) (list 1 1) (list 2 0)))
(define data-B (list (list 0 0) (list 1 1.1) (list 2 0.1)))

(define filt-A (map (lambda (r) (topo/vietoris-rips data-A r)) (list 0.5 1.0 1.5)))
(define filt-B (map (lambda (r) (topo/vietoris-rips data-B r)) (list 0.5 1.0 1.5)))

(define pers-A (topo/persistence filt-A))
(define pers-B (topo/persistence filt-B))

(define similarity (topo/bottleneck pers-A pers-B))

similarity  ; Small value → similar shape
```

